metadata:
  type: [ verb ]
details: |-
  # What is 하게체? {#what-is-하게체?}

  <f>하게체</f> is used to familiarly address someone without lowering oneself. It can be used to show respect when the other
  person is of lower social standing but not necessarily young in absolute age.

  You will encounter <f>하게체</f> in situations such as a father-in-law and mother-in-law using the form with their son-in-law,
  an uncle using it with a grown nephew with children, or two brother-in-laws speaking with each other.

  You will still hear <f>하게체</f> used in daily conversation but it has a slightly archaic tone, so it will usually only
  be used by older people. A young person speaking using <f>하게체</f> will tend to sound quite awkward.
  :source[https://namu.wiki/w/하게체]
